Preconditions:
- The input array `strs` is not null.
- The length of `strs` is greater than 0.
- All strings in `strs` have the same length.
- Each string in `strs` consists of lowercase English letters.

Postconditions:
- The returned value is an integer representing the minimum number of deletion indices required to make the final array lexicographically sorted.
- The final array after deletions has its elements in lexicographic order.
- The final array has the same length as the original array `strs`.